    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nI was attempting to use `except? SIZE_MAX` but it doesn't seem supported.\r\n\r\nSo I tried `except? 2**64-1` which generates invalid C code:\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror: indirection requires pointer operand ('int' invalid)\r\n      __pyx_r = ((2 ** 64) - 1);\r\n```\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\r\ncdef unsigned long foo(int i) except? 2**64-1:\r\n    if i:\r\n        raise ValueError\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n_No response_\n\n### Environment\n\nCython version 0.29.30\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This one is a quick way of getting it working (assuming two's complement, which is ubiquitous anyway)\r\n```\r\ncdef unsigned long foo(int i) except? <unsigned long>-1:\r\n    if i:\r\n        raise ValueError\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlternatively, use this one. Note I'm using `ULONG_MAX` because your return type is `unsigned long`. Otherwise, you should be returning type `size_t` and use `SIZE_MAX` for flagging exception value.\r\n\r\n```\r\ncdef extern from \"<limits.h>\":\r\n    const unsigned long ULONG_MAX\r\n\r\ncdef unsigned long foo(int i) except? ULONG_MAX:\r\n    if i:\r\n        raise ValueError\r\n```\r\n",
